title.97: Star Wars: Tales of the Jedi (1993) #3

description.4: Doctor Strange and Doctor Doom duel for the Oculus!
description.5: The conclusion is here! But this is just the beginning for the Man Without Fear!
description.9: ""Garth"" leads Daimon through the inner bowels of Hell as part of a twisted tour. But Daimon's guide wears a false face…
description.11: The Vulture flies once more! Adrian Toomes escapes prison to find a cure for his cancer...and he's prepared to cut down anyone who gets in his way! Aunt May breaks some difficult news to Peter.
description.12: What is the Uni-Mind of Lemuria? And how can the Avengers go up against an intangible force? Plus, Goliath and Black Knight have a Battle Royale with two members of Delta Force!
description.13: It's a Summers family reunion! Cyclops, Jean Grey, Professor X, and Cable's son Tyler face off against the resurrected Stryfe- in control of Cable's body! Can these telepathic titans save Cable from Stryfe's control...or will Cable have to pay the ultimate price for him to be stopped?
description.14: The Sidewinder attacks! When the Star-Spangled Soldier least suspects it, one of his deadliest foes will make a crushing move! Plus: Diamondback returns from Wakanda!
description.15: In his desperate struggle for the Elixir of Life, Gambit becomes a prisoner in the depths of Candra's Petite Chou club!
description.17: Thanos assembles an elite team of cosmic villains to acquire the Oracle of Ancient Knowledge! Featuring Geatar, Rhino, Nitro, and Super-Skrull!
description.18: The stunning conclusion to Spider-Woman's battle with Deathweb.
description.29: Namorita is no more. In her place is the blue-skinned Kymaera, and she is strong and mighty for whatever the future holds!
description.32: Nomi Sunrider begins her Jedi training.
description.34: Final Issue! The Avengers West Coast are no more. But there will always be a place for heroes. What will become of the former members of the Avengers West Coast?
description.35: Pip enters a duel of mortal combat to save the Watch from the wrath of angry trolls!
description.39: Daredevil's list of problems keeps growing and growing! To find the Snakeroot, he may have to seek out the help of Morbius the Living Vampire. He must also face the Snakeroot's warped doppelganger of the woman he loved- Elektra. And worst of all, his secret identity is on display in the newspapers for all the world to see!
description.42: Ambushed by Trauma! The old nemesis of Hulk's friends the Pantheon is out for revenge, and the Hulk is caught in the crossfire! Can Hulk and the Pantheon stop Trauma - without any casualties of their own?
description.43: Issue #300 celebration! Stark leads the Iron Legion against Ultimo, the living holocaust! Guest appearance by War Machine!
description.47: Thor's rampage is taking him dangerously close to Asgard...but first Nidgar Keep must pay the price!
description.49: The team remains divided on how best to handle Haven, a new ""prophet"" bearing a strange ""messiah"" that threatens to usher in ""humanity's rebirth"".
description.52: Happy X-Giving! After the months of hardship, the team finally takes a breather. Which is the perfect opportunity for a marriage proposal!
description.58: The Abomination tells a depressed woman the fairytale version of his life, as well as his unusual origin.
description.66: Salome reclaims the power of the Sorcerer Supreme!
description.67: Enter the Kingpin! What will this mean for a young Daredevil?
description.70: Gambit returns to New Orleans to discover that his wife, Bella Donna Bordeaux, is in a coma! The only way to revive her is with the Elixir of Life- an item possessed by the Eternals!
description.73: Deathweb moves in for the kill as Spider-Woman struggles to come out on top.
description.75: It's time for the next wave of Secret Defenders to enter the fray! NORTHSTAR, and his blinding speed! NOVA, and his cosmic power! THE INCREDIBLE HULK, and his smashing strength! Together with Doctor Strange, the Sorcerer Supreme, these heroes will face the worst villain in all of the Marvel Universe - THANOS, the Mad Titan!
description.76: Spider-Man's sentence has been passed...and it's execution! But will the Jury be able to commit Spidey to death while Venom is still at large? Mary Jane makes a pivotal decision about her health.
description.78: The Avengers receive a distress call from Lemuria, a Deviant city. Unfortunately, the Avengers have fallen into a trap, and only Sersi escapes the mind control of "brain mines"! Enter Delta Force, the team of Deviant heroes tasked to save the Avengers!
description.79: STRYFE LIVES! With the body of Nathan Summers under his control, Stryfe begins his assault on Cable's life and friends! Only one hope remains for Cable- his parents, Cyclops and Jean Grey of the X-Men! And Cable's wayward son Tyler learns the truth of his father's origin- but can he survive Stryfe's ambush?
description.80: It's Captain America versus Namor, the Sub-Mariner! Read as Marvel takes you back to 1941, before the Invaders formed. Plus: Namor attacks President Roosevelt! Can Cap hope to calm the Sub-Mariner before America goes to war with Atlantis?
description.84: The Mountain of Judgement awaits. Vying for salvation from eternal damnation, Daimon and his demonic crew climb every mountain to spare themselves a fate worse than death.
description.85: Take a deep dive into acclaimed Avengers events the ‘Kree-Skrull War’ and ‘Operation: Galactic Storm’! Get an inside look at these major cosmic crusades with this archive of the key players, enemies and battles! Earth’s history with the Kree is documented here!
description.90: Justice is served with the return of Vance Astrovik!
description.97: Bogga the Hutt is on the hunt for Adegan crystals and a family that includes a Jedi Knight is in his crosshairs.

1.text: Siryn is tricked by Juggernaut and her dying uncle, Black Tom Cassidy! Will she handle her family issues without turning to the bottle?

6.text: The sheriff has made a mistake by cooping up Punisher in a cell…a horrible, grave mistake.

7.text: The Seekers are becoming a problem, and the unlikely team of Darkhawk and Venom work together to take them down.

8.text: Trieste Rahn and Namor fight the behemoth mutant Xlyym.

10.text: Mr. Sinister unleashes his plans against the X-Men! Season 2 starts here!

16.text: The Scarlet Witch’s nightmares become reality as she faces Master Pandemonium in Unity, New England. Will the delusional Master possess Wanda at long last? Plus, the town of Unity dislodges from the rest of America, becoming a floating island!

17.text: Thanos assembles an elite team of cosmic villains to acquire the Oracle of Ancient Knowledge! Featuring Geatar, Rhino, Nitro, and Super-Skrull!

18.text: The stunning conclusion to Spider-Woman's battle with Deathweb.

19.text: Starhawk and Aleta battle it out in a bid for total control.

20.text: Venom runs afoul of Morbius the Living Vampire!

21.text: Is Mort's job working for Death turning him away from his old, human self?

22.text: THE FALL OF THE HAMMER PART 4 Doom 2099 must unite with 2099’s X-Men, Punisher, Spider-Man, and Ravage, to take down villains posing as Asgardian gods. Will this be a battle worthy of Valhalla? And do these imposters have the divine powers they claim to possess?

23.text: THE FALL OF THE HAMMER PART 5 One for all? Will Jake Gallows, Punisher 2099, play nice with his new teammates? The Fall of the Hammer event continues as Punisher, along with 2099’s X-Men, Spider-Man, and Doom, save Asgard from Alechemax!

24.text: As Luke leads the Rebel fleet on its escape to its new base on Hoth, the Rebels' new allies, the Mon Calamari, plan a diversion to help them escape an Imperial blockade. But the Imperials soon realize that the Mon Calamari attacks are a diversion for the real Rebel escape, and they set off with the intent of destroying the Rebels once and for all. Meanwhile, Han, Chewie, and C-3PO take off in the Millennium Falcon to find an alternate escape route to Hoth, but what they discover is a seemingly impassable route that would take them dangerously close to a gigantic stellar flare!

25.text: After a series of fighting and defeating, the X-Men have one final battle--but can anyone beat the notorious Thor?

26.text: Question: What's more terrifying than the Punisher? Answer: an army of Punishers!

27.text: Re-live the origin of Spider-Man as brought to you by Stan Lee, John Romita and Larry Lieber! Plus, a collection of iconic moments from the wall-crawler’s history!

28.text: Hawkeye finds himself caught in a struggle for survival against the (original) Secret Empire!

29.text: Namorita is no more. In her place is the blue-skinned Kymaera, and she is strong and mighty for whatever the future holds!

30.text: Before he was the scourge of the underworld, Frank Castle was a soldier struggling to survive against all odds in Vietnam! Read about Castle's pre-Punisher days here!

31.text: While at Empire State University, Captain Marvel must combat racism and violence brought on by the Sons of the Serpent.

33.text: The Infinity Watch arrives in Asgard with a dire warning for Odin about his son.

34.text: Final Issue! The Avengers West Coast are no more. But there will always be a place for heroes. What will become of the former members of the Avengers West Coast?

35.text: Pip enters a duel of mortal combat to save the Watch from the wrath of angry trolls!

36.text: Phineas Horton was like a modern day Prometheus, stealing fire from heavens and handing a human torch down to man.  Writer, Kurt Busiek, and Artist, Alex Ross, tells the origin of The Human Torch in stunning detail.  Don't miss out on this Epic storytelling event in Book I of Marvels!

37.text: THE RISE OF THE HAMMER Jordan Boone lets slip a valuable secret on Alchemax, and his lack of discretion costs him dearly. What is the Valhalla Project Boone spoke of? Miguel discovers that Lyla may have significant technical errors, while Conchata O’ Hara investigates Spider-Man on her own terms. Who are these new incarnations of Thor and Heimdall? And are they really immortal beings of Asgard?

41.text: Ant-Man: Scott Lang infiltrates the Time Variance Authority! Will the Fantastic Four ever wipe themselves clean from the TVA’s records? Mobius M. Mobius cannot let that be allowed.

45.text: Punisher is in a skyscraper full of mobsters and figures the best way to bring them all down is to blow it up, even though he is still inside.

46.text: PLATOON! THE ONE MAN KILLING MACHINE! Spider-Man and Iron fist team up against Platoon who along with A.R.M.S is getting ready for a field demonstration of Platoon armor.

53.text: Lady Deathstrike has returned, with designs on taking Wolverine's Adamantium for herself. Unfortunately for her, Logan has recenty been separated from his Adamantium quite forcefully by Magneto. Can Wolverine hold her off without his Adamantium-laced skeleton and a reduced healing factor?

54.text: Sabretooth's imprisonment at the X-Mansion raises concerns for the team.

56.text: Thor’s coming for Thanos...! But Silver Surfer and the Mind Valkyrie know how outmatched the Thunder God might be, so they rush to Thanos’ ship before any serious harm is done!

57.text: Loki enlists the help of Pluto to dispatch his brother Thor, who subcontracts the Asgardian demon Hrinmeer to end the God of Thunder. But when Pluto double-crosses Loki, will the brothers team-up?

58.text: The Abomination tells a depressed woman the fairytale version of his life, as well as his unusual origin.

59.text: Carnage plots his clever escape after his MAXIMUM CARNAGE killing spree!

60.text: Can Captain America stop the Red Skull using a thought-gone power from WWII?

61.text: Arcade is one messed up menace- if Shatterstar and Adam X don't kill one another, then Shatterstar's wife will pay with her life! In Ireland, Siryn and Warpath are greeted by some unwanted company at Cassidy Keep…

68.text: With Punisher believed dead under a collapsed building, Lynn and Payback begin trying to fill his shoes.

69.text: Haven, the host of the Adversary, professes their innocence. But her actions speak otherwise.

71.text: Scarlet Witch takes the stage in her own titular mini-series. After being plagued by horrifying nightmares, Wanda Maximoff seeks the mystical aid of mentor Agatha Harkness. Can Harkness unlock the inner sanctum of Wanda’s mind? And what hardships will Scarlet Witch endure when she discovers she is a ‘Nexus Being’?

73.text: Deathweb moves in for the kill as Spider-Woman struggles to come out on top.

74.text: The Guardians are shocked when they discover that Yondu's planet has been distorted beyond recognition.

75.text: It's time for the next wave of Secret Defenders to enter the fray! NORTHSTAR, and his blinding speed! NOVA, and his cosmic power! THE INCREDIBLE HULK, and his smashing strength! Together with Doctor Strange, the Sorcerer Supreme, these heroes will face the worst villain in all of the Marvel Universe - THANOS, the Mad Titan!

77.text: Two eternal enemies of the Prince of Asgard and the Lion of Olympus join forces!

81.text: Three “Strangers” unite against the unholy power of Salome!

82.text: The Warriors feel the force of Psionex! Asylum steps out for the first time in his new super-powered identity.

83.text: Death's Head II fights the villainous Collapsar to the death, while Dark Angel discovers that Mys-Tech is responsible for the destruction on Eopia.

85.text: Take a deep dive into acclaimed Avengers events the ‘Kree-Skrull War’ and ‘Operation: Galactic Storm’! Get an inside look at these major cosmic crusades with this archive of the key players, enemies and battles! Earth’s history with the Kree is documented here!

86.text: Don't miss this epic season final issue!

87.text: After mobsters decide to end their Punisher problem, Frank destroys their Manhattan tower and apparently dies along with them. This brings the unwanted attention of the F.B.I. and V.I.G.I.L. However, Punisher is not dead, and he struggles to remove himself from the rubble.

88.text: It's Venom vs. Juggernaut in the finale of "The Madness!" But Brock must also confront the psychic demons that are laying waste to his mind!

89.text: The start of a pulse-pounding mini-series starring Marvel's premiere archer Avenger!

91.text: The X-Men attempt to rescue Storm from Shinobi Shaw. Meanwhile, Hydra holds Banshee’s old Interpol pal hostage!

92.text: In search of his missing father, Darkhawk finds himself in San Francisco. But instead of his father, he stumbles upon a different familiar face…Venom!

93.text: Bloodhawk is taken by La Lunatica to be delivered to the Theatre of Pain! But we soon learn that La Lunatica isn't as villainous as we thought!

94.text: Mort starts his new job.  Unlike most teenagers who get a job at a supermarket or a restaurant, Mort gets a job working under Death himself!

95.text: Spider-Man 2099 must keep his identity safe from co-worker Anna Coye, but will Miguel O’Hara’s secret lead to Anna’s demise? (Note: this issue does not contain the Hulk 2099 story in the original print version.)

96.text: Scott Summers and Jean Grey’s pre-wedding spotlight! Jubilee’s flippant attitude on love is changed when she reads Jean’s old diary. Witness Jean and Scott’s relationship as told through memories, and get an inside peek at the X-Men’s most memorable romance.

98.text: Going against the UN's orders, the Avengers team arrives on Genosha. Soon after arriving, the team is met with a powerful man with a familiar vendetta against humans. It seems the team may be in for the fight of their lives!

99.text: Former Weapon-X project Maverick begins his merciless hunt for Sabretooth. Will the X-Men be able to assist in his endeavor? And with Wolverine in Japan, will the news of Creed’s rampage reach Logan too late? Guest-starring Rogue, Bishop, and Gambit, as they try to stop Sabretooth dead in his tracks!
